  <prompt>At the `TenantCache` wrapper layer (`src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Infrastructure/Cache/TenantCache.cs`), emit SECONDARY metrics with `resource` dimension via NEW Counters `cache.hits.by_resource` + `cache.misses.by_resource`. Register on the canonical static `CacheMetrics` class (from task 002). `resource` is the natural resource name in the cache key (e.g., `session`, `document-analysis`, `embedding`, `graph-token`, `membership`). Primary `cache.hits` / `cache.misses` from the MetricsDistributedCache decorator layer remain UNCHANGED. Different metric names → no double-counting. No cardinality cap (NFR-06): code-driven natural bounding ~10-20 expected.</prompt>
  <role>Senior .NET developer with OTel Metrics. Apply `task-execute` skill at FULL rigor.</role>
  <goal>`TenantCache` emits `cache.hits.by_resource` + `cache.misses.by_resource` with `resource` dimension on every hit/miss path. Primary decorator-layer metrics unchanged. Build clean; tests at baseline. KQL verification deferred to task 030.</goal>
  <context>
    <background>Spec FR-03: R1 amendment to ADR-009 dropped per-tag dimensions (resource, op) because dimension cardinality was theoretically unbounded at the decorator layer. R2 reintroduces `resource` ONLY at the TenantCache wrapper where the resource name is part of the cache key shape `tenant:{tid}:{resource}:{id}:v{n}` — naturally bounded by code (~10-20 distinct resource names). Different metric names mean we don't double-count or interfere with the primary decorator-layer metrics.</background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Infrastructure/Cache/TenantCache.cs (MODIFY)</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Telemetry/CacheMetrics.cs (EXTEND — add `cache.hits.by_resource` + `cache.misses.by_resource` counters)</file>
    </relevant-files>
  </context>
  <constraints>
    <constraint source="spec">FR-03 — secondary counters at TenantCache layer; resource dimension; bounded code-driven cardinality.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec">NFR-06 — no soft cap on resource dimension cardinality.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-009">No silent in-memory fallback; metrics must be observable.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-029">Publish-size ≤+0.5 MB (NFR-04).</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-032">Symmetric DI preserved.</constraint>
  </constraints>
