  </knowledge>
  <steps>
    <step order="1">Read TenantCache.cs to find the hit/miss decision points. Cache key shape `tenant:{tid}:{resource}:{id}:v{n}` means `resource` is available as a parameter to TenantCache methods.</step>
    <step order="2">Add two new Counters to canonical `CacheMetrics` static class: `cache.hits.by_resource` + `cache.misses.by_resource` (both `Counter&lt;long&gt;`).</step>
    <step order="3">In TenantCache hit path: call `CacheMetrics.RecordHitByResource(resource)`. In miss path: `CacheMetrics.RecordMissByResource(resource)`.</step>
    <step order="4">Confirm resource value passed is the LOGICAL resource name (e.g., "session", "embedding") not the full key. If TenantCache's API does not surface resource as separate param, lift it from the key parse helper.</step>
    <step order="5">Build: `dotnet build src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/` — 0 errors.</step>
    <step order="6">Run BFF unit tests; no regressions expected (additive change).</step>
    <step order="7">Update TASK-INDEX 🔲 → ✅.</step>
    <step order="8">Step 9.5 quality gates: code-review + adr-check.</step>
  </steps>
  <tools>
    <tool name="Read">TenantCache + CacheMetrics</tool>
    <tool name="Edit">TenantCache.cs + CacheMetrics.cs</tool>
    <tool name="Bash">dotnet build + test</tool>
  </tools>
  <outputs>
    <output type="code">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Infrastructure/Cache/TenantCache.cs (MODIFIED)</output>
    <output type="code">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Telemetry/CacheMetrics.cs (EXTENDED with by_resource counters)</output>
  </outputs>
  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">CacheMetrics has 2 new Counters: cache.hits.by_resource + cache.misses.by_resource.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">TenantCache emits both on every hit/miss path with the logical resource name.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Primary cache.hits / cache.misses at decorator layer unchanged.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">dotnet build clean; tests at baseline.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">KQL `customMetrics | where name == 'cache.hits.by_resource' | summarize sum(value) by tostring(customDimensions.resource)` returns rows with bounded resource values post-deploy (verified at task 030).</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>
